content: Have you considered adding a mode so you could invite friends to join, basically a virtual putting league. That would be awesome.
Great app for beginners

not sure why other reviews are saying you cant leave the app. I change apps all the time while im using it with no problems. I think that its user error, and those other peoples phones not working correctly, not the app. As long as you dont clear all your windows, it swaps from app to app just fine. I love the app and use it on a daily basis for putting practice. I recommend it to anyone that needs putting practice, but putting is just boring. This app adds some fun to the monotonous nature of putting practice

I really like the idea if this app! I want this to be able toedit after the round is over and I want to simply be able to check a text and be able tome back to it! Also if the game could be extended out to include circle 2 would be nice! I find it to be a huge slapp in the face by the people that made this app that some of these issues have not been resolved or even commented on in the rating section if your not going to update it and make it worth the money then make it free for people to use!

Unless you put in all your scores while staying in the app, your entire game is erased or changed. Switch apps to send a text message? Gone. Take a screenshot? Gone. Sometimes it looks like it's working and you hit next, then your score gets screwed up. I'm done until this is fixed.

Nice game play. However, the app could use some loving care - looks like it was last updated years ago. Read other posts for enhancement ideas such as keeping hand going after answering a text, multi player duels, more stats, etc.
Fun game, useful tool. Poor app, you can't leave the app and can't edit/delete scores in the app.

Waste of $2.99. This is a paid app with the worst user interface I've ever used. You can't leave the APP and come back to it and continue to putt. Absolutely lazy. The most effort went into how the app is used. Garbage. Worst part is the putt game is a blast. Hasn't been updated since 2017. Why would sponsored pros get behind this outdated nonsense?
Game is fun, app is hot garbage. Doesn't always save rounds but will sometimes save partial rounds that you can never delete. No multiplayer so no easy way to putt with a friend. Very frustrating.

Love the idea of the app. The game itself has already helped my putting. However there is need for some improvements. Like others have stated, it'd be nice to edit games after they've completed as they sometimes close before I complete a game. It'd also be nice if there was a multiplayer mode as this would be fun to play with more people.

Appreciate the app. Happy to throw a couple bucks to the developers. If you have a round going and have to leave the app (like getting a phone call) when you come back, the round is saved and locked out. There is no way to then go back and finish round. Can't edit or delete results so it is hard to track progress with multiple incomplete rounds you can't delete. It would also be nice to track results by profile.
Good app and a fun game, but you really need a way to delete scores.
Absolute in love with this app.. Daily use Essential for disc golf players Easy to use and navigate Cant wait to see how they continue to improve this already amazing app
Finish button and cumulative stats would be a nice add.
Why does this cost money? No statistics other than high scores? Good idea and start of a project- but this needs at least a little bit more work before its worth paying for.

Great app. Only complaint is there is no finish round button. It's also annoying because you can't edit your round and it likes to exit out of your round in the middle and it's not editable after that point...super frustrating. It also Sucks that you can't delete the partial rounds that are auto saved and uneditable. Sucks that I paid money for a half assed app

Really nice look and feel, needs updates. - 2 player mode for head to head - ability to edit to correct for entering error - delete games where a screen time out records a false low score - would be nice to have stats (games, averages, at each distance, etc) and also allow 1st half and second half comparisons. Thanks for creating this! Tom in 'Tosa Wisconsin
Just lazily done app for the price..
How do you save a score? I finished my game and there is no save button so I went back to the menu and my game was gone.
I enjoy using the app. It gets you out putting with a purpose. I highly recommend buying this more than affordable app.

Great game, terrible app. There is no way to back out of or delete an accidental round. Tried to show my friend how it worked and now I have a lovely 65 in my scores table. Unacceptable for a purchased app.

Great practice game, decent implimentation. Can't understand why scores aren't editable after the fact or why they added so much 'swipe to...' It's extremely easy to accidentally exit a card early and not be able to return to it to edit. Fewer swipe features amd editting ability please!
Great app for getting out of a slump and adding some excitement for putting. Any chance of an add friends feature in the future to create mini competitions amongst friends?

Like most people have already said, basic game but even still minor things like not being able to delete a partial round that happens by accidentally swiping is not good. Global rankings would be nice by QoL improvements need to be done first.

Great idea and fun to play, but app randomly doesn't save my scores. Also no way to delete a partial round. A finish round button after round two should exist instead of having to hit back. Swiping controls are not intuitive. Would be even better if it tracked stats and had to the ability to compare scores online with friends or geographical areas.

As others have said this is great - really good idea and very fun to play. However the lack of basic features like deleting a partial round are annoying. Normally I would rate an clearly incomplete app like this 2 or 3 stars but am giving it 4 because I like the idea and it gets me out putting every single day.

Would appreciate having the notification bar remain visible. It makes it very difficult to switch between apps without it. Also the "feature" that reverts to the main screen if you swipe down is awful. Somehow checking notifications backs you out of a game and no data is saved? That's a fault, not a feature.

Not bad, fun game for practice. Interface can be frustrating, If you hit the wrong button you can end your round, and can't go back in to edit or delete partial rounds. Need option to change distances, need more gameplay options in general.

Super, user friendly app! The extra points make me try hard to sink the 1st & last putts... Plus it's a great confidence builder, for the moment, when you need it the most! Under $5!!! ðŸ¤¯ Want to improve your putting??? Download the app today!
Doesn't save games accurately
Needs stats, but otherwise a good practice tool.
Fun app, would be 5 stars if I could delete scores where I couldn't finish the round, or delete scores from previous years so I only see the rounds I want.
How much for the ability to delete or modify a round?
Fun, but how hard can it be to make it possible to clear unfinished/accidentaly exited rounds?!
Would've given this 5 stars if there was an option to delete scorecards. Also didn't realize that there were two parts to each round, hence the wanting to delete scorecards.

This app has already improved my putting in 3 days... Trying to get a higher score makes me stay out and practice much longer... If they added a few more games and had a few ui improvements it would be perfect
Great concept but not the best UI. Could add a few buttons to make the experience better
I thought I can play this together with my neko son... Back to the paper version, or am I missing something???
Please make it so that multiple can play as well as make it so that you can edit/delete old score cards PLEASE also add the stats for andriods
Awesome game need to make for multiple play

5 star ideas, 1 star execution. The scoring is fun, addictive and well thought out. The app in general is clunky, basic, and lacks basic things. The app needs to track stats, tell me what % of putts I make from 10, 15, etc. I use this on the course and have to transfer my data to excel when I get home. Keep updating!
Wish the app saved rounds after each station. If you accidently exit out you lose your score and have to start over

I like how if you dont do too good you have another try to save that round but my only problem is that I cant figure out how to delete the scores that it saved in the middle of round but overall it's a great app and I love it thank you so much for creating this
A paid app where you can't save scores or track stats... no thanks.
Excellent scoring app for putting practice!

Glorified calculated. I keep wishing it did so much more. Biggest feature it is missing is the ability to delete rounds that never got finished. I also wish it kept track for my statistics for each distance and my first/ last percentage. The last thing I'm wanting is to be able to sort scores by user to see progress.
Awesome way to improve your putting. Wishing for a few more features and a way to save your history when you change devices.
Fun game to pratice putting with yourself or a buddy.
This app is a great practice tool for building confidence and skill in your circle one putting.
Love it but was wondering if we can customize the distance I can't get 30' in my basement, I'm able to get up 25
Good start, but needs some work. None of my scores save and I cant see anyone else's scores either. Also more stat tracking would be nice.

App could use some quality of life updates, but the game is great, and the app works fine. Suggestions: save incomplete round. Even if it's just after the first half. Also after game having a "main menu" option. Right now the only options are start a new game or go back. I want to see where that score ranks on my leader board. Great game! Love it!

I like the game, good for practice. But it could use more features. Should be able to trend performance over time, see % made from each distance. Also be able to categorize results based on type of basket used, or wind conditions etc. Should be easy features to add.

I love what the app is, however, there are a few things that need updated for it to get 5 stars. I do not like that if you accidentally swipe out of scores you have to restart the round again. There needs to be an option to continue editing a current round and to delete rounds. I currently have incomplete rounds that it will not let me delete. Also, I would recommend marking which score is the most recent, or adding times with dates so you can compare, in case you do more than one round in a day.

It's a fun putting game. However, it would be better if it included the ability to customize the game. Everyone has their personal opionion in regards to productive putting practice methods. Having the option to reflect these different methods would enhance this app. I would get rid of the reward for "last putt made". Actual disc golf play does not allow for practice putts from one spot.
great for practice!

This is a great tool to help out with putting. I wish you could add players 
to where it was player v player. Either way awesome app.

Overall it's a good app but It never keeps a history of my scores so I can 
track progress.
How do you play this game? How many putts from each distance? I must be missing something because  I can't find this info anywhere. Thus basic info should be in the tutorial.
Great app and alot of fun. I don't like that if you accidentally back out it it stops your current game
Brest app to help your putting! Use it consistently (everyday) and you'll see improvements with a week!
Super simple and easy to use. Will help put a little more pressure on each shot if you like to score well.
Thank you for making this app.  Its been my favorite putting game for years!
Can't wait for the update! This game is perfect for practicing. Also a good format for a putting tournament.
I love it
A fun app to improve your putting game! If your friend is too broke/cheap to buy the app, you can download it on another device that shares the same email.
I would love it we could see a record of our past games.
Idea for future update, add an option to score more than 1 player. Otherwise, fun little putting game.
